text: John David Baker (born 4 January 1951) is a male former diver who competed for Great Britain and England. Baker represented Great Britain in the men's 3 metre springboard at the 1972 Summer Olympics. He also represented England in the 3 metres springboard, at the 1970 British Commonwealth Games in Edinburgh, Scotland. ==References== Category:1951 births Category:English male divers Category:Divers at the 1970 British Commonwealth Games Category:Divers at the 1972 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic divers of Great Britain Category:Living people
